Key Match Events: Lebanon and China played out a goalless draw
Khalil Khamsi’s early header was collected safely by China goalkeeper Yan Junling
Hasan Maatouk’s shot hit the crossbar
Lui Bin Bin’s effort was punched away by Lebanese custodian Mostafa Matar
China’s Zhang Linpeng forced a save from Lebanon’s goalkeeper
Hasan Srour’s right-footed shot was denied by China’s Yan Junling
Wu Lei’s close-range effort was cleared off the line by Lebanon’s defense
Post-Match Reflections: Lebanon coach Miodrag Radulovic remained positive
China coach Aleksandar Jankovic emphasized the importance of self-reliance
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at Al Thumama Stadium
Both Lebanon and China saw several efforts being thwarted as well as missed
Others: The match was part of the AFC Asian Cup Qatar 2023 Group A
Tajikistan, China, and Lebanon still have opportunity to reach the last 16
Qatar became the first side to advance as Group A winners
Lebanon and Tajikistan will square off in their final group match on Monday
China will face hosts and defending champions Qatar next Monday
